(
  'Calvia''s Best Coffee Shops and Brunch Spots for 2026',
  'calvia-best-coffee-shops-brunch-spots-2026',
  'The specialty coffee and brunch scene in Calvia has exploded. From artisan roasters to Instagram-worthy brunch menus, here are the must-visit spots.',
  '<p>Calvia''s coffee scene has transformed in recent years. Where once your options were limited to a cafe con leche at a hotel buffet, the municipality now boasts specialty coffee shops, artisan roasters, and brunch destinations that would hold their own in any European capital.</p>

<h2>Specialty Coffee</h2>
<p>Bean &amp; Gone in Santa Ponsa is the standard-bearer for specialty coffee in Calvia. Using single-origin beans from a Palma-based roaster, they produce espresso and filter coffee that satisfies even the most discerning coffee enthusiasts. The flat white is consistently excellent, and the cold brew during summer months is refreshingly well-balanced. The minimalist interior, friendly staff, and reliable Wi-Fi make it a favorite with remote workers.</p>
<p>Cafe Arabesco in Portals Nous brings Middle Eastern coffee traditions to Mallorca, offering Turkish coffee, Arabic-spiced lattes, and a selection of teas alongside excellent pastries. The courtyard seating is especially pleasant on winter mornings.</p>

<h2>Best Brunch Spots</h2>
<p>The Boat House in Puerto Portals has become synonymous with upscale brunch in Calvia. Their smashed avocado on sourdough with poached eggs and dukkah is a signature, and the acai bowls are vibrant and generously portioned. Weekend reservations are essential from April through October.</p>
<p>Lila Portals in Portals Nous offers a more relaxed, bohemian brunch experience. Homemade granola, freshly baked banana bread, and smoothie bowls are popular choices. The plant-filled terrace feels like a secret garden, and prices are more gentle than the marina-front competition.</p>

<h2>Traditional Mallorcan Morning</h2>
<p>For an authentic local experience, several village bakeries serve the traditional Mallorcan breakfast of ensaimada with a hot chocolate. Ca''n Joan de S''Aigo, with its nearest branch in Palma, is legendary, but Calvia''s own Forn de Pa in Santa Ponsa produces ensaimadas that rival the capital''s best: light, flaky, and subtly sweet.</p>

<h2>Remote Work Friendly</h2>
<p>If you are working remotely in Calvia, Co-Coffee in Palmanova combines a specialty coffee bar with a co-working space. The coffee is excellent, the Wi-Fi is fast and reliable, and the day-pass pricing is reasonable. It has become a hub for the growing community of digital nomads who have made Calvia their base.</p>',
